 and opportunities created by heritage tourism and the development of the town as a "home" for German Americans. These interconnected stories illuminate what it means to belong to a place and why the Texas Hill Country has become the spiritual, if not actual, home of many people.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCountry lifezTexaszTexas Hill Country. 0aFamilieszTexaszTexas Hill Country. 0aGerman AmericanszTexaszTexas Hill Country. 0aHomezTexaszTexas Hill Country. 0aPlace (Philosophy). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/77746040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292798977423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292798977/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK